HEADWORD: Tetrazone
<hw>Tet"ra*zone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a certain series of basic compounds containing a chain
of four nitrogen atoms; <as>for example, ethyl <ex>tetrazone</ex>,
<chform>(C2H5)2N.N2.N(C2H5)2</chform>, a colorless liquid having an odor
of leeks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

